1
00:00:02,289 --> 00:00:04,410
[Shaun] After six open houses,

2
00:00:04,495 --> 00:00:07,716
I am sure that
"fixer-upper" means decrepit.

3
00:00:07,859 --> 00:00:10,804
Well, part of the fun is imagining
what something could be.

4
00:00:10,889 --> 00:00:13,283
It could be expensive

5
00:00:13,391 --> 00:00:16,741
and messy and loud
and even dangerous.

6
00:00:17,820 --> 00:00:18,899
[Sighs]

7
00:00:18,984 --> 00:00:21,018
Hey, why don't you do
your thing with the real estate agent?

8
00:00:21,102 --> 00:00:22,351
I'm gonna go wander.

9
00:00:24,124 --> 00:00:25,445
Hi.

10
00:00:25,530 --> 00:00:27,358
Tori Vargas. Any questions?

11
00:00:27,443 --> 00:00:28,953
Oh, yes, I have many.

12
00:00:29,038 --> 00:00:31,406
About school districts,
drought-tolerant landscaping,

13
00:00:31,491 --> 00:00:32,851
seismic retrofitting...

14
00:00:32,936 --> 00:00:35,062
Someone came prepared.

15
00:00:35,147 --> 00:00:36,601
Does that include
loan pre-approval?

16
00:00:36,686 --> 00:00:38,492
- If not, I can help.
- Oh, no.

17
00:00:38,577 --> 00:00:41,804
Going to open houses out of
our price range is our new hobby,

18
00:00:41,889 --> 00:00:43,586
and sometimes,
there are cookies.

19
00:00:43,671 --> 00:00:46,656
How fun!
Uh, excuse me just a sec.

20
00:00:47,628 --> 00:00:48,978
Hi, there.

21
00:00:50,910 --> 00:00:53,303
[Quirky music playing]

22
00:01:03,607 --> 00:01:06,480
I grew up with a reading nook
just like this one.

23
00:01:06,565 --> 00:01:10,124
I'd lay in a pile of pillows,
watch the falling snow.

24
00:01:10,525 --> 00:01:14,051
That sounds... uncomfortable.

25
00:01:14,136 --> 00:01:16,234
A lot of the work
is just cosmetic.

26
00:01:16,319 --> 00:01:17,890
I could do most of it myself.

27
00:01:17,975 --> 00:01:20,023
Make it a perfect family home.

28
00:01:20,269 --> 00:01:22,204
Like, these window frames
are just painted shut,

29
00:01:22,296 --> 00:01:24,343
but all you have to do is...

30
00:01:26,456 --> 00:01:29,765
- Ow! Damn it.
- See?

31
00:01:30,552 --> 00:01:32,132
Dangerous.

32
00:01:33,276 --> 00:01:34,276
Forks and knives?

33
00:01:34,361 --> 00:01:35,553
Hands only.

34
00:01:35,638 --> 00:01:37,921
And don't you drown
my shao bing in hot sauce.

35
00:01:38,451 --> 00:01:40,093
- Yes, ma'am.
- [chuckles]

36
00:01:42,416 --> 00:01:45,376
A scallion omelet
and sesame flatbread.

37
00:01:45,461 --> 00:01:47,640
Mm! Did I forget
an anniversary?

38
00:01:49,874 --> 00:01:52,810
This is a thank-you for
planning our first road trip.

39
00:01:56,267 --> 00:01:57,267
Mm!

40
00:01:57,670 --> 00:01:59,164
I'm planning more road trips.

41
00:01:59,249 --> 00:02:00,367
[Chuckles]

42
00:02:00,538 --> 00:02:02,714
I can't wait
to head south on PCH.

43
00:02:02,859 --> 00:02:05,570
Last trip was a solo one
on my Ducati.

44
00:02:05,681 --> 00:02:06,812
Hold on.

45
00:02:06,897 --> 00:02:07,898
[Chuckles]

46
00:02:07,983 --> 00:02:09,210
You're a biker chick?

47
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:11,718
Was. In another life.

48
00:02:12,975 --> 00:02:14,335
You miss it?

49
00:02:14,995 --> 00:02:16,460
The other life?

50
00:02:16,591 --> 00:02:20,179
Motorcycles are too dangerous.
You could end up paralyzed.

51
00:02:20,264 --> 00:02:22,222
[Chuckles] Nice deflection.

52
00:02:22,460 --> 00:02:23,828
[Sighs]

53
00:02:24,150 --> 00:02:26,132
I didn't know you
in the other life.

54
00:02:26,788 --> 00:02:28,484
I like this one.

55
00:02:31,707 --> 00:02:34,054
Still feel that way
if I go get the hot sauce?

56
00:02:36,106 --> 00:02:39,765
[Gentle music playing]

57
00:02:40,506 --> 00:02:41,882
[locker door closes]

58
00:02:47,257 --> 00:02:49,406
We haven't had a chance
to talk about...

59
00:02:49,491 --> 00:02:50,999
You kissing me.

60
00:02:51,084 --> 00:02:54,265
Thereby crossing a line
you said we shouldn't cross,

61
00:02:54,428 --> 00:02:56,299
right as I
was headed on a date.

62
00:02:56,384 --> 00:02:57,777
[Chuckles nervously]

63
00:02:58,384 --> 00:02:59,578
How'd that go?

64
00:02:59,798 --> 00:03:01,007
Great.

65
00:03:02,288 --> 00:03:03,882
I barely heard a word he said,

66
00:03:03,967 --> 00:03:08,031
because the whole time,
I was thinking about our kiss.

67
00:03:09,161 --> 00:03:11,117
It was... It was amazing.

68
00:03:12,522 --> 00:03:14,679
Yes, it was.

69
00:03:15,739 --> 00:03:17,984
Look, I like you,

70
00:03:18,391 --> 00:03:20,460
but I need some clarity here.

71
00:03:21,908 --> 00:03:22,909
Right.

72
00:03:24,362 --> 00:03:25,648
Let me be clear.

73
00:03:26,498 --> 00:03:29,501
How about I make you dinner
tomorrow, my place,

74
00:03:29,847 --> 00:03:31,617
and we talk about
where we're headed?

75
00:03:34,895 --> 00:03:36,249
Sounds good.

76
00:03:37,007 --> 00:03:38,476
It's a date then.

77
00:03:39,130 --> 00:03:40,578
A date.

78
00:03:40,959 --> 00:03:44,453
[Gentle music playing]

79
00:03:48,239 --> 00:03:49,312
Oh.

80
00:03:49,397 --> 00:03:50,876
Good morning, Dr. Lim.

81
00:03:50,961 --> 00:03:52,890
Did Clay stay over last night?

82
00:03:53,046 --> 00:03:54,679
- He did.
- Excellent.

83
00:03:54,764 --> 00:03:58,476
That means you are likely in a good
mood and amenable because of the sex.

84
00:03:58,958 --> 00:04:00,326
Amenable to what?

85
00:04:00,411 --> 00:04:02,148
I think you will like it.

86
00:04:03,323 --> 00:04:04,641
[Dr. Glassman]
There was movement,

87
00:04:04,725 --> 00:04:06,585
flexion, and lateral rotation,

88
00:04:06,670 --> 00:04:09,429
which means that there was
engagement with the psoas

89
00:04:09,514 --> 00:04:12,585
and the glutes,
and I saw it twice.

90
00:04:13,026 --> 00:04:15,968
Signals are getting through
to your spinal column.

91
00:04:17,138 --> 00:04:19,273
[Shaun] This deformity
is not just scar tissue.

92
00:04:19,358 --> 00:04:20,679
It's a compressive syrinx.

93
00:04:20,764 --> 00:04:22,257
We can enter from
a mid line myelotomy

94
00:04:22,342 --> 00:04:25,203
and drain the fluid
after we de-tether your cord.

95
00:04:27,437 --> 00:04:28,438
I could...

96
00:04:28,870 --> 00:04:30,406
You could walk again.

97
00:04:32,429 --> 00:04:35,039
Audrey, this approach
is much safer

98
00:04:35,124 --> 00:04:36,984
than the one
we discussed last time.

99
00:04:38,544 --> 00:04:40,720
[Gentle music playing]

100
00:04:44,435 --> 00:04:46,390
I need time to think it over.

101
00:04:47,031 --> 00:04:48,359
Of course.

102
00:04:52,414 --> 00:04:56,296
Okay, today is the first day I will
be implementing my new system.

103
00:04:56,381 --> 00:04:58,949
I'm sure you agree
it is a major improvement.

104
00:04:59,043 --> 00:05:00,859
I don't know what the hell
you're talking about.

105
00:05:00,943 --> 00:05:03,598
My new rating system
for first-year residents?

106
00:05:03,683 --> 00:05:05,468
I e-mailed you multiple drafts.

107
00:05:05,553 --> 00:05:07,492
You never responded.

108
00:05:07,577 --> 00:05:08,742
Once all the data is in,

109
00:05:08,827 --> 00:05:10,351
I will share
the completed version.

110
00:05:10,436 --> 00:05:12,242
Well, can't wait.

111
00:05:13,461 --> 00:05:14,461
[Elevator bell dings]

112
00:05:15,172 --> 00:05:17,914
[Up-tempo music plays]

113
00:05:20,620 --> 00:05:22,495
- [Chuckles] Whoa!
- [laughs]

114
00:05:22,580 --> 00:05:23,902
When I asked to see
where you worked,

115
00:05:23,986 --> 00:05:24,996
I didn't mean it
as a challenge.

116
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:28,031
I had to get you on the mat to see
if you exaggerated on your profile.

117
00:05:28,116 --> 00:05:30,370
I'm... I'm not really a fan
of walks on the beach.

118
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:31,673
Whoa! [Chuckles]

119
00:05:31,834 --> 00:05:33,479
Sunsets are overrated.

120
00:05:33,564 --> 00:05:34,776
All right.

121
00:05:37,333 --> 00:05:38,682
Whoa!

122
00:05:39,424 --> 00:05:41,003
Nice.

123
00:05:42,434 --> 00:05:44,269
- [Grunts]
- [coughs]

124
00:05:46,001 --> 00:05:47,176
[Chuckles]

125
00:05:47,691 --> 00:05:48,823
[Grunts]

126
00:05:48,908 --> 00:05:51,190
What happens on a third date?

127
00:05:51,275 --> 00:05:52,406
[Breathes heavily]

128
00:05:53,612 --> 00:05:54,612
Lily?

129
00:05:55,475 --> 00:05:56,737
Lily?

130
00:05:56,981 --> 00:05:58,975
[Tense music playing]

131
00:05:59,924 --> 00:06:01,274
Are you okay?

132
00:06:01,627 --> 00:06:03,655
<i>Opening theme music playing...</i>

133
00:06:03,740 --> 00:06:05,740
<font color=#FF00FF>*THE GOOD DOCTOR*</font>
<font color=#00FF00>Season 06  Episode 09</font>

134
00:06:05,824 --> 00:06:08,144
Episode Title: <font color=#FFc30f>"Broken or Not"</font>
Aired on: <font color="#00ffff">December 12, 2022.</font>

135
00:06:08,389 --> 00:06:10,758
<font color=#ffc30f>Synchronized</font> by <font color=#00FF00>srjanapala</font>

136
00:06:11,317 --> 00:06:12,500
[elevator bell dings]

137
00:06:13,028 --> 00:06:15,427
My new system has over
50 unique metrics

138
00:06:15,512 --> 00:06:16,510
{\an8}that go into your scores.

139
00:06:16,595 --> 00:06:18,301
{\an8}Everything you do
will be assessed.

140
00:06:18,386 --> 00:06:20,466
{\an8}Everything? Uh, could you be
a bit more specific?

141
00:06:20,551 --> 00:06:21,262
{\an8}No.

142
00:06:21,347 --> 00:06:22,910
{\an8}Is this like
a head-to-head competition?

143
00:06:22,995 --> 00:06:23,973
{\an8}It's designed to make you aware

144
00:06:24,058 --> 00:06:26,019
{\an8}of your individual
strengths and weaknesses.

145
00:06:26,104 --> 00:06:28,005
Residents with more strengths
are more likely

146
00:06:28,090 --> 00:06:30,254
to get invited back
for a full residency.

147
00:06:33,834 --> 00:06:35,923
Hi, Teddy. Dr. Powell.

148
00:06:36,761 --> 00:06:38,276
What happened to your head?

149
00:06:38,361 --> 00:06:41,363
I idiotically smacked myself
with a 20-pound kettle bell.

150
00:06:41,448 --> 00:06:43,583
Kettlebell injuries
are surprisingly common.

151
00:06:43,668 --> 00:06:45,060
My gym has a printout

152
00:06:45,172 --> 00:06:46,892
of ten different ways
you can hurt yourself.

153
00:06:47,106 --> 00:06:48,544
Did you witness the accident?

154
00:06:48,629 --> 00:06:50,614
Yeah. I'm there
for all his workouts.

155
00:06:50,699 --> 00:06:51,636
Oh, so you're his trainer.

156
00:06:51,721 --> 00:06:52,766
His brother.

157
00:06:52,851 --> 00:06:54,592
My <i>baby</i> brother.

158
00:06:54,677 --> 00:06:56,357
{\an8}He's got a real knack
for making me suffer.

159
00:06:58,223 --> 00:06:59,249
All right.

160
00:06:59,423 --> 00:07:02,168
We're gonna run a full
concussion protocol

161
00:07:02,406 --> 00:07:04,480
and get a CT as a precaution.

162
00:07:06,274 --> 00:07:08,262
Not until
we take care of this gash.

163
00:07:09,694 --> 00:07:11,957
You're also experiencing
abdominal pain.

164
00:07:12,131 --> 00:07:13,473
{\an8}- Did that pain start...
- Aah!

165
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:15,523
{\an8}...before or after
you hit your head?

166
00:07:15,608 --> 00:07:18,738
{\an8}Uh, kind of simultaneous?

167
00:07:19,510 --> 00:07:21,386
{\an8}Do you mind lifting your shirt?

168
00:07:28,586 --> 00:07:30,283
Teddy, you've recently
lost a lot of weight.

169
00:07:30,367 --> 00:07:31,716
Seventy pounds.

170
00:07:31,801 --> 00:07:32,978
In five months.

171
00:07:33,152 --> 00:07:34,849
Getting that summer
beach bod ready.

172
00:07:35,023 --> 00:07:37,207
Keeping the T-shirt on for now.

173
00:07:39,463 --> 00:07:41,364
Teddy, do you mind
if we laid you back

174
00:07:41,449 --> 00:07:42,890
just to get a better look?

175
00:07:42,975 --> 00:07:44,890
[Tense music playing]

176
00:07:52,416 --> 00:07:54,418
- [Grunts]
- Oh, got a lump.

177
00:07:54,655 --> 00:07:57,137
An inguinal hernia.
It's not reducible.

178
00:07:57,324 --> 00:07:59,191
I think it's also strangulated.

179
00:08:03,090 --> 00:08:06,004
Hmm, Dr. Perez is right.

180
00:08:06,096 --> 00:08:08,373
The blood flow to your herniated
intestine has been cut off.

181
00:08:08,457 --> 00:08:11,707
You need immediate surgery. Okay.

182
00:08:13,453 --> 00:08:15,824
[Tense music playing]

183
00:08:18,955 --> 00:08:21,434
This is Lily.
37, dizziness, epistaxis,

184
00:08:21,519 --> 00:08:22,715
purulent nasal discharge.

185
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:24,910
Let's get full labs
including blood cultures.

186
00:08:26,248 --> 00:08:28,165
I guess the upside
of dating a doctor

187
00:08:28,250 --> 00:08:30,137
is no waiting in the ER.

188
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:36,488
I dated a guy at the DMV
for that very reason.

189
00:08:36,868 --> 00:08:38,645
Do you have a history
of nosebleeds?

190
00:08:38,730 --> 00:08:39,731
Yes.

191
00:08:39,816 --> 00:08:40,750
Part of my perpetual

192
00:08:40,835 --> 00:08:42,168
sinus infection.

193
00:08:42,253 --> 00:08:44,536
I've been on and off
antibiotics for a year.

194
00:08:44,621 --> 00:08:47,161
I figured it's because
I teach Kung Fu to kids.

195
00:08:47,246 --> 00:08:48,838
Mm, adorable.

196
00:08:48,923 --> 00:08:50,491
Do you feel any sinus pressure?

197
00:08:50,583 --> 00:08:52,582
Also, how'd you two meet?

198
00:08:53,841 --> 00:08:56,402
Yes, and Bumble?

199
00:08:56,487 --> 00:08:58,358
Thank you, Dr. Reznick.
I got this.

200
00:08:58,736 --> 00:09:01,215
He's worried this will be
awkward because I'm his ex.

201
00:09:01,447 --> 00:09:03,114
Don't worry. We're friends now.

202
00:09:03,340 --> 00:09:05,355
Any other recent symptoms?

203
00:09:06,593 --> 00:09:08,116
I've had a few migraines

204
00:09:08,297 --> 00:09:10,301
and bad taste
in my mouth recently.

205
00:09:10,386 --> 00:09:12,465
Temp's elevated,
and she's hypertensive.

206
00:09:12,578 --> 00:09:15,348
Acute-on-chronic
bacterial rhinosinusitis?

207
00:09:15,907 --> 00:09:17,598
Probably,
but given the headaches,

208
00:09:17,683 --> 00:09:19,038
I want a stat
brain and sinus CT

209
00:09:19,123 --> 00:09:20,863
with and without contrast.

210
00:09:20,955 --> 00:09:22,392
[Monitor beeping]

211
00:09:22,653 --> 00:09:25,046
[Shaun] Hernia is reduced.

212
00:09:25,220 --> 00:09:27,440
Next step in the tension-free
hernioplasty?

213
00:09:27,540 --> 00:09:29,832
[Powell and Perez] Use mesh
to cover the fascial defect.

214
00:09:30,214 --> 00:09:31,824
By strengthening
the inguinal floor,

215
00:09:31,909 --> 00:09:33,955
we hope to prevent
further hernias.

216
00:09:34,332 --> 00:09:37,980
No extra credit will be given
for statements of the obvious.

217
00:09:41,705 --> 00:09:43,465
It's impressive how much
weight Teddy's lost.

218
00:09:43,620 --> 00:09:45,451
I just hope he's doing it
for the right reasons.

219
00:09:45,535 --> 00:09:46,894
Hard to see a wrong reason.

220
00:09:47,068 --> 00:09:48,724
He was clearly
pretty overweight.

221
00:09:48,809 --> 00:09:49,897
[Shaun] I agree.

222
00:09:50,071 --> 00:09:52,641
Obesity increases
health risks for diabetes,

223
00:09:52,726 --> 00:09:54,902
heart disease,
and some cancers.

224
00:09:54,987 --> 00:09:58,729
Fair. But our culture can really
go overboard on the fat-shaming,

225
00:09:59,152 --> 00:10:01,708
which can lead to
low self-esteem, depression,

226
00:10:01,793 --> 00:10:03,223
none of which is healthy.

227
00:10:03,308 --> 00:10:06,887
Trying to change to please
someone else rarely works.

228
00:10:07,045 --> 00:10:08,699
Getting someone you love

229
00:10:08,784 --> 00:10:11,637
to do what is best for them
is a good thing.

230
00:10:13,180 --> 00:10:16,183
There's ectopy in the EKG.
QT looks prolonged.

231
00:10:16,576 --> 00:10:19,002
Push 2 grams IV of magnesium.

232
00:10:19,087 --> 00:10:20,436
[Monitor alarm]

233
00:10:21,106 --> 00:10:23,150
He's going into torsades.

234
00:10:23,235 --> 00:10:24,483
Proper response?

235
00:10:24,568 --> 00:10:25,648
Synchronized cardioversion.

236
00:10:26,151 --> 00:10:28,066
Yes. Prepare to shock him.

237
00:10:30,068 --> 00:10:31,156
[Defibrillator whirs]

238
00:10:31,658 --> 00:10:33,863
Charging 200 joules. Clear.

239
00:10:34,247 --> 00:10:35,247
[Beep]

240
00:10:38,475 --> 00:10:40,041
[Alarm stops, beeping resumes]

241
00:10:42,210 --> 00:10:44,160
Good catch, Dr. Powell.

242
00:10:45,344 --> 00:10:47,246
I caught
the strangulated hernia.

243
00:10:47,815 --> 00:10:50,942
Teddy's arrhythmia is likely a
sign of an underlying condition.

244
00:10:51,027 --> 00:10:52,394
It could be quite dangerous.

245
00:10:52,479 --> 00:10:54,679
Next, you will be assessed on
how quickly and accurately

246
00:10:54,764 --> 00:10:56,078
you can determine
what's causing it.

247
00:10:56,162 --> 00:10:57,590
Suture scissors.

248
00:11:07,714 --> 00:11:10,137
I'll start with the sinuses.

249
00:11:10,325 --> 00:11:12,113
Hey, I found you
a new prospect.

250
00:11:12,458 --> 00:11:15,071
Unless your last date was a
love connection for the ages.

251
00:11:15,156 --> 00:11:17,028
- That's a no.
- Oh. Hmm.

252
00:11:17,113 --> 00:11:20,725
How terrible for him.
How exciting for me.

253
00:11:20,810 --> 00:11:23,480
Berkeley law grad,
former fitness model,

254
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:26,019
just moved back
to the valley from Paris.

255
00:11:26,149 --> 00:11:28,105
Thanks, but I'll pass.

256
00:11:30,258 --> 00:11:32,208
That's severe opacification.

257
00:11:32,293 --> 00:11:34,340
Sinus mucosa's thickened.

258
00:11:34,448 --> 00:11:36,363
There's already bony erosion.

259
00:11:36,559 --> 00:11:37,826
Lily needs endoscopic

260
00:11:37,911 --> 00:11:39,605
sinonasal debridement.

261
00:11:39,690 --> 00:11:42,591
He's smart, he's ripped,
he's worldly,

262
00:11:42,676 --> 00:11:44,577
and unlike Perez,
he's available.

263
00:11:44,751 --> 00:11:46,560
- We kissed.
- What?

264
00:11:46,645 --> 00:11:47,848
You and Perez?

265
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:48,752
Yeah.

266
00:11:48,836 --> 00:11:50,785
What about his
recovery-related boundaries?

267
00:11:50,870 --> 00:11:52,380
I haven't figured that out yet,

268
00:11:52,465 --> 00:11:56,418
but he did invite me
to dinner at his place.

269
00:11:58,059 --> 00:12:00,058
I'm exploring.

270
00:12:01,252 --> 00:12:04,496
Just be careful, okay?

271
00:12:04,684 --> 00:12:06,160
Okay.

272
00:12:09,827 --> 00:12:12,387
Her sinus infection spread
through her skull base.

273
00:12:12,668 --> 00:12:15,216
That's a massive
6x4 centimeter abscess.

274
00:12:15,342 --> 00:12:17,293
Page Park. If that
thing ruptures, she'll die.

275
00:12:17,378 --> 00:12:19,554
Lily needs sinus
and brain surgery.

276
00:12:20,945 --> 00:12:23,930
[Tense music playing]

277
00:12:24,431 --> 00:12:26,647
[Monitor beeping]

278
00:12:26,772 --> 00:12:29,012
[Dr. Park] Sinus debridement
looks very good, Dr. Allen.

279
00:12:29,313 --> 00:12:31,103
[Jordan] Pulling the scope.

280
00:12:31,241 --> 00:12:33,504
Bacitracin-coated Telfa.

281
00:12:33,589 --> 00:12:37,351
And we use two burr holes to drain
the abscess using ultrasound guidance.

282
00:12:37,436 --> 00:12:39,220
[Drill whirs]

283
00:12:42,254 --> 00:12:44,064
[Asher] So,
how'd you get approval

284
00:12:44,149 --> 00:12:45,931
to operate on your
new girlfriend?

285
00:12:46,016 --> 00:12:49,126
Two dates does not equal a
girlfriend. No approval necessary.

286
00:12:50,459 --> 00:12:52,097
[Asher] Trajectories look good.

287
00:12:52,182 --> 00:12:53,712
Drainage tool.

288
00:12:54,558 --> 00:12:57,540
Plus or minus that you got to
parade her in front of Morgan?

289
00:12:57,771 --> 00:12:59,270
Definitely not parading,

290
00:12:59,355 --> 00:13:01,107
and Morgan and I are...

291
00:13:02,341 --> 00:13:04,392
friends, so neither.

292
00:13:04,557 --> 00:13:05,837
Uh-huh.

293
00:13:07,985 --> 00:13:10,570
Mm, this is as much
as I can get

294
00:13:10,655 --> 00:13:12,701
without risking rupture
into the ventricle.

295
00:13:12,786 --> 00:13:14,938
Eh, the rest is up
to the antibiotics.

296
00:13:15,023 --> 00:13:16,415
Leave the drain and close.

297
00:13:18,487 --> 00:13:19,900
Would you say

298
00:13:19,985 --> 00:13:21,611
you loved, liked, or hated

299
00:13:21,696 --> 00:13:22,752
the last house we saw?

300
00:13:22,926 --> 00:13:24,667
Are those the only options?

301
00:13:24,841 --> 00:13:26,280
I should examine your hand.

302
00:13:26,365 --> 00:13:27,583
Oh, it's fine.

303
00:13:27,757 --> 00:13:30,307
I can't stop thinking
about the crown molding

304
00:13:30,392 --> 00:13:31,196
and the reading nook,

305
00:13:31,370 --> 00:13:32,632
so as long
as you don't hate it,

306
00:13:32,717 --> 00:13:34,510
I'm thinking we should
talk to a mortgage broker

307
00:13:34,594 --> 00:13:36,501
about making an offer.

308
00:13:38,747 --> 00:13:40,575
You said going to open houses

309
00:13:40,660 --> 00:13:42,267
was only for fun.

310
00:13:42,352 --> 00:13:44,272
I've looked at our finances,
and we can swing it.

311
00:13:44,357 --> 00:13:45,750
Rent is spent.

312
00:13:45,835 --> 00:13:48,018
A mortgage payment is...

313
00:13:48,103 --> 00:13:49,659
whatever rhymes with payment

314
00:13:49,744 --> 00:13:51,306
and...
And means good investment.

315
00:13:51,768 --> 00:13:54,206
My research shows
we should adhere

316
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:58,102
to the 28/36 rule with regards
to monthly pre-tax income.

317
00:13:58,187 --> 00:14:00,308
You have swelling around
your second digit's metacarpal

318
00:14:00,392 --> 00:14:01,854
and the proximal phalanx
of your thumb.

319
00:14:01,938 --> 00:14:03,479
Okay, I've done worse
on engine blocks.

320
00:14:03,564 --> 00:14:07,057
Shaun, we can be homeowners.

321
00:14:07,232 --> 00:14:09,431
Doesn't that
excite you even a little?

322
00:14:09,529 --> 00:14:10,529
Hmm.

323
00:14:11,095 --> 00:14:14,649
I am a little excited
that you are excited.

324
00:14:14,806 --> 00:14:16,719
Good, because I made
an appointment

325
00:14:16,893 --> 00:14:18,156
with a mortgage broker.

326
00:14:18,330 --> 00:14:20,845
And you guys can talk 25/36.

327
00:14:25,702 --> 00:14:27,103
Twenty-eight.

328
00:14:32,999 --> 00:14:35,306
[Cell phone buzzes, chimes]

329
00:14:39,849 --> 00:14:42,744
[Gentle music playing]

330
00:14:53,575 --> 00:14:55,534
You know, it's silly
for us to be competitive.

331
00:14:55,724 --> 00:14:58,127
Said the loser while losing.

332
00:14:58,627 --> 00:15:00,502
Olive branch.

333
00:15:00,587 --> 00:15:03,241
I don't know what's
causing the arrhythmia. Do you?

334
00:15:03,415 --> 00:15:04,776
I have ideas.

335
00:15:06,162 --> 00:15:07,859
O-kay.

336
00:15:07,944 --> 00:15:11,078
So you can present them
and land the knockout blow...

337
00:15:11,252 --> 00:15:13,377
if you're confident
that you're right.

338
00:15:14,090 --> 00:15:16,259
- Or?
- Or we can bounce ideas off each other,

339
00:15:16,344 --> 00:15:18,065
get the right answer,
and help this guy.

340
00:15:19,409 --> 00:15:21,454
For all we know,
one of Dr. Murphy's metrics

341
00:15:21,539 --> 00:15:24,705
is cooperation
amongst colleagues.

342
00:15:26,374 --> 00:15:27,375
Fine.

343
00:15:27,460 --> 00:15:28,460
But I present.

344
00:15:29,270 --> 00:15:31,272
Do you have any idea
how often women

345
00:15:31,357 --> 00:15:32,706
get zero credit
for their ideas,

346
00:15:32,791 --> 00:15:34,823
even when they come
out of their mouths?

347
00:15:35,087 --> 00:15:36,932
Fine.

348
00:15:37,030 --> 00:15:39,857
Blood sample showed critically
low potassium and sodium,

349
00:15:39,942 --> 00:15:42,347
which makes no sense
given the power-food diet

350
00:15:42,432 --> 00:15:43,737
that his brother's got him on.

351
00:15:43,822 --> 00:15:44,651
There's plenty of nutrients.

352
00:15:44,736 --> 00:15:47,280
- So maybe celiac.
- Mm.

353
00:15:47,382 --> 00:15:50,767
IgA and IgG antibody tests
were normal.

354
00:15:51,205 --> 00:15:53,440
I'm thinking
primary aldosteronism.

355
00:15:54,284 --> 00:15:55,760
That's interesting.

356
00:15:56,032 --> 00:15:59,775
Please present your ideas on what
is causing our patient's arrhythmia.

357
00:16:01,837 --> 00:16:05,948
We think that Teddy
has primary aldosteronism.

358
00:16:06,033 --> 00:16:08,079
Explains initial
electrolyte levels and...

359
00:16:08,909 --> 00:16:10,572
[quirky music playing]

360
00:16:12,741 --> 00:16:16,031
That doesn't align with urine
studies or lack of hypertension.

361
00:16:16,116 --> 00:16:17,407
This was your idea.

362
00:16:17,492 --> 00:16:19,338
Congenital long QT syndrome.

363
00:16:19,423 --> 00:16:21,183
Teddy's QT levels
have returned to normal,

364
00:16:21,268 --> 00:16:22,844
and he has no family history.

365
00:16:22,929 --> 00:16:27,133
He has critically low levels of
potassium, sodium, and magnesium.

366
00:16:27,285 --> 00:16:29,321
I noticed that.
Despite a good diet.

367
00:16:29,406 --> 00:16:31,407
It suggests absorption and...

368
00:16:33,813 --> 00:16:36,685
What happened to cooperation
amongst colleagues?

369
00:16:36,859 --> 00:16:38,891
I didn't realize
you were gonna be wrong.

370
00:16:40,572 --> 00:16:42,947
Slight enamel erosion
on the molars

371
00:16:43,032 --> 00:16:45,368
and trauma to the oral mucosa.

372
00:16:46,237 --> 00:16:50,067
And these tiny abrasions on
his knuckles are from his teeth.

373
00:16:50,152 --> 00:16:52,259
Self-induced vomiting
led to malnutrition,

374
00:16:52,344 --> 00:16:53,915
which caused the arrhythmia.

375
00:16:54,455 --> 00:16:56,758
Teddy, you are bulimic.

376
00:16:57,078 --> 00:17:01,680
[Tense music playing]

377
00:17:04,555 --> 00:17:06,508
That's quite the cocktail.

378
00:17:06,593 --> 00:17:09,929
Not the kind I was hoping
we'd share, but here we are.

379
00:17:10,694 --> 00:17:13,008
Not exactly what I would
have worn either.

380
00:17:13,100 --> 00:17:16,148
We're hoping the antibiotics will
clear the remaining infected areas

381
00:17:16,233 --> 00:17:17,886
of your sinuses and brain.

382
00:17:18,975 --> 00:17:22,226
I feel like I'm already getting
the VIP treatment from you.

383
00:17:22,863 --> 00:17:24,560
Dr. Reznick was right.

384
00:17:24,695 --> 00:17:26,958
She said your flower game
was very solid.

385
00:17:30,104 --> 00:17:31,369
She stopped by?

386
00:17:31,454 --> 00:17:32,454
Yes.

387
00:17:33,506 --> 00:17:36,017
Ostensibly to check on me,

388
00:17:36,571 --> 00:17:38,760
but mostly
to sing your praises.

389
00:17:39,236 --> 00:17:41,970
Not many guys
have an ex as a hype man.

390
00:17:42,359 --> 00:17:44,010
Lucky me.

391
00:17:49,807 --> 00:17:51,760
I think it's too soon
to discharge Teddy.

392
00:17:51,934 --> 00:17:54,765
He has responded well
to electrolyte replacement,

393
00:17:54,850 --> 00:17:56,420
there are no signs
of recurrent arrhythmia,

394
00:17:56,504 --> 00:17:59,705
and the hernioplasty only
requires simple wound care.

395
00:18:00,234 --> 00:18:02,036
- He's bulimic.
- I know.

396
00:18:02,121 --> 00:18:03,644
I diagnosed him, thank you,

397
00:18:03,729 --> 00:18:06,073
after you and Dr. Powell
failed to.

398
00:18:06,158 --> 00:18:09,877
Eating disorders have the highest
mortality rate of any mental illness.

399
00:18:10,731 --> 00:18:13,821
I referred him
for a psych consult

400
00:18:13,906 --> 00:18:16,396
and provided a list of clinics
for eating disorders.

401
00:18:16,481 --> 00:18:19,018
He needs help now,
not in a few weeks.

402
00:18:19,438 --> 00:18:22,185
Give me some time. Maybe I can get
psych to talk to him before he leaves.

403
00:18:22,269 --> 00:18:25,142
Points are given
for passion and commitment

404
00:18:25,316 --> 00:18:27,588
and taken away for arguing
with an attending.

405
00:18:27,673 --> 00:18:28,873
I don't care about the points.

406
00:18:30,582 --> 00:18:33,324
We can't keep him hospitalized

407
00:18:33,498 --> 00:18:36,416
without a clear
surgical indication.

408
00:18:38,643 --> 00:18:39,992
[Sighs]

409
00:18:43,769 --> 00:18:45,075
Stop hounding me.

410
00:18:45,249 --> 00:18:47,338
I'm having a coffee.
Can I have a coffee?

411
00:18:47,512 --> 00:18:48,612
You're hovering.

412
00:18:48,697 --> 00:18:50,647
I'm excited about the prospect

413
00:18:50,732 --> 00:18:52,863
of getting you
back on your feet.

414
00:18:52,948 --> 00:18:54,432
[Sighs]

415
00:18:54,606 --> 00:18:57,174
This surgery
is not an easy decision.

416
00:18:57,596 --> 00:18:59,119
The surgical plan
is a very good one.

417
00:18:59,293 --> 00:19:01,877
Yes, it's a solid plan.

418
00:19:02,024 --> 00:19:03,024
But?

419
00:19:04,093 --> 00:19:08,271
But my life is good right now,
really good.

420
00:19:08,356 --> 00:19:09,748
Better than it's been
in a while.

421
00:19:09,997 --> 00:19:11,859
And the idea of that
changing is...

422
00:19:11,944 --> 00:19:14,261
Lea said we would go to
open houses as a fun hobby,

423
00:19:14,346 --> 00:19:15,760
but now she wants to buy one.

424
00:19:15,845 --> 00:19:17,885
- Shaun, I'm in the middle of a...
- No, you're not.

425
00:19:22,939 --> 00:19:25,760
[Exhales sharply] A house?
Okay, well, congratulations.

426
00:19:25,845 --> 00:19:27,682
Look at you two, grown-up-ing.

427
00:19:27,822 --> 00:19:29,940
No, it's a fixer-upper.

428
00:19:30,032 --> 00:19:31,938
Dr. Glassman, I don't like it.

429
00:19:32,055 --> 00:19:33,767
Did you tell Lea that?

430
00:19:33,852 --> 00:19:37,853
No, she is excited when she talks
about the house. It makes her happy.

431
00:19:37,938 --> 00:19:40,704
And I think
she has been sad lately.

432
00:19:40,789 --> 00:19:42,141
Why has she been sad?

433
00:19:42,257 --> 00:19:44,595
I told you,
we have to wait to get pregnant

434
00:19:44,680 --> 00:19:46,581
because of her
Asher man's syndrome.

435
00:19:46,952 --> 00:19:51,688
Well, maybe Lea is looking for
a way to move you two forward.

436
00:19:52,122 --> 00:19:55,819
You think if we buy that house,

437
00:19:55,904 --> 00:19:57,430
Lea will be less sad?

438
00:19:57,515 --> 00:20:00,008
I don't know, but, you know,
buying a house can be exciting.

439
00:20:00,093 --> 00:20:01,776
It's a distraction.
Distractions can be useful.

440
00:20:01,860 --> 00:20:03,869
No, no, no.
I do not like distractions.

441
00:20:04,101 --> 00:20:05,578
Shaun... [sighs]

442
00:20:05,733 --> 00:20:08,102
You've been rating residents
for quite a while now,

443
00:20:08,187 --> 00:20:10,193
and now all of a sudden,
you revamp your entire system?

444
00:20:10,277 --> 00:20:12,017
When did you decide to do that?

445
00:20:12,138 --> 00:20:14,321
Mm, after the sextuplets
were born.

446
00:20:14,489 --> 00:20:16,125
Wasn't that
around the same time

447
00:20:16,228 --> 00:20:18,318
you found out about
Lea's Asher man's?

448
00:20:18,403 --> 00:20:19,752
Yes.

449
00:20:19,980 --> 00:20:22,125
We were both very sad.

450
00:20:24,071 --> 00:20:27,728
You think my new system
was a distraction?

451
00:20:27,813 --> 00:20:29,994
Yeah, and... and now
maybe Lea needs one.

452
00:20:30,458 --> 00:20:32,765
Oh, excellent idea. [Chuckles]

453
00:20:33,126 --> 00:20:34,908
Thank you, Dr. Glassman.

454
00:20:35,418 --> 00:20:38,722
[Quirky music playing]

455
00:20:43,945 --> 00:20:45,730
Brought your ride outta here

456
00:20:46,091 --> 00:20:49,206
and your discharge papers.

457
00:20:49,645 --> 00:20:51,895
Pulled some strings,
got you a psych consult

458
00:20:51,980 --> 00:20:53,879
at an eating-disorder clinic
day after tomorrow.

459
00:20:54,113 --> 00:20:56,566
Thanks, but I'm good.

460
00:20:56,651 --> 00:20:59,816
This hospital stay
was the wake-up call I needed.

461
00:21:01,612 --> 00:21:03,902
You don't have to
go through this alone.

462
00:21:04,967 --> 00:21:08,057
Discharge party.
I brought drinks.

463
00:21:08,142 --> 00:21:10,934
Special Potassium Powerhouse
for my big bro.

464
00:21:12,067 --> 00:21:14,699
So, um, Teddy tells me
he has some, like,

465
00:21:14,784 --> 00:21:16,816
freak electrolyte deficiency?

466
00:21:17,421 --> 00:21:18,726
Do you know what caused it?

467
00:21:19,899 --> 00:21:21,673
Teddy's got
all the information.

468
00:21:22,708 --> 00:21:25,337
Do I need to make
any adjustments to his diet?

469
00:21:25,977 --> 00:21:28,619
It might be a good time to dial
back on the weight-loss goals.

470
00:21:28,703 --> 00:21:30,017
Uh, why?

471
00:21:30,149 --> 00:21:31,626
Simon, uh, let's just go.

472
00:21:31,711 --> 00:21:33,841
Is it dangerous
for him to diet now?

473
00:21:33,926 --> 00:21:35,231
For how long?

474
00:21:35,316 --> 00:21:37,928
Um, I-I-I can't really say.

475
00:21:38,063 --> 00:21:40,367
Simon, forget it.

476
00:21:40,541 --> 00:21:41,939
It's on me
to make sure you're okay.

477
00:21:42,023 --> 00:21:44,399
No, it's actually not.
It's my life.

478
00:21:44,484 --> 00:21:46,311
Why are you getting mad at
me? I'm just being supportive.

479
00:21:46,395 --> 00:21:48,289
Otherwise known as
micromanaging everything I do.

480
00:21:48,373 --> 00:21:50,940
You were miserable
and a mess, okay?

481
00:21:51,334 --> 00:21:52,574
I'm the one
getting you healthy.

482
00:21:56,647 --> 00:21:58,065
What am I missing?

483
00:22:00,213 --> 00:22:01,479
Tell him.

484
00:22:06,577 --> 00:22:09,378
It wasn't your workouts
that took off the weight.

485
00:22:10,694 --> 00:22:12,214
I've been...

486
00:22:13,065 --> 00:22:14,503
purging.

487
00:22:17,738 --> 00:22:19,464
Making myself puke.

488
00:22:20,407 --> 00:22:22,190
[Somber music playing]

489
00:22:27,593 --> 00:22:30,759
Is that what caused
your heart thing?

490
00:22:32,486 --> 00:22:34,525
Why would you
do something so stupid?

491
00:22:34,610 --> 00:22:37,346
Maybe because you're so obsessed
with me not being a fat embarrassment.

492
00:22:37,430 --> 00:22:38,870
- I never said that.
- You didn't have to.

493
00:22:38,954 --> 00:22:40,424
You've never been so excited

494
00:22:40,509 --> 00:22:42,159
as when I mentioned
maybe losing some weight.

495
00:22:42,243 --> 00:22:44,955
- Because I'm worried about you?
- You're ashamed of me.

496
00:22:45,552 --> 00:22:46,992
It's been years
since we've hung out,

497
00:22:47,174 --> 00:22:48,916
and now every day,

498
00:22:49,014 --> 00:22:50,798
you're all over me
to meet you at the gym.

499
00:22:50,883 --> 00:22:53,681
You're killing yourself,
but this is my fault?

500
00:22:54,969 --> 00:22:58,174
Get your own ride home.
I don't want to micromanage.

501
00:23:00,039 --> 00:23:01,408
Sim...

502
00:23:06,452 --> 00:23:07,655
Teddy, I am so sorry.

503
00:23:07,740 --> 00:23:08,740
It's fine.

504
00:23:10,552 --> 00:23:11,947
I can Uber.

505
00:23:17,367 --> 00:23:20,038
- You sent her flowers from me?
- You're welcome.

506
00:23:20,123 --> 00:23:22,516
Have you considered that I may
not even want to keep seeing Lily?

507
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:25,287
She's clearly a keeper,
and you need a girlfriend.

508
00:23:25,372 --> 00:23:26,749
How is that your business?

509
00:23:26,834 --> 00:23:27,901
Because I need
you and I not to make

510
00:23:27,985 --> 00:23:29,813
the same mistake
all over again.

511
00:23:30,073 --> 00:23:32,142
We both know we've been teetering
on the edge of falling back into us.

512
00:23:32,226 --> 00:23:33,416
You're out of your mind.

513
00:23:33,523 --> 00:23:34,635
Like you haven't
thought about it?

514
00:23:34,719 --> 00:23:36,028
You read too much
into my friendly gestures.

515
00:23:36,112 --> 00:23:37,367
Like offering me your sperm?

516
00:23:37,452 --> 00:23:38,869
For IVF.

517
00:23:38,954 --> 00:23:41,439
Could the symbolism
be any more heavy-handed?

518
00:23:42,662 --> 00:23:44,011
We can't go back.

519
00:23:44,096 --> 00:23:45,974
You made it very clear
that I'm not what you wanted,

520
00:23:46,058 --> 00:23:47,233
and I haven't changed.

521
00:23:47,407 --> 00:23:48,931
So I need you to move on.

522
00:23:53,631 --> 00:23:55,720
[Cell phone buzzes]

523
00:23:55,894 --> 00:23:58,026
[Tense music playing]

524
00:24:00,364 --> 00:24:02,017
- How long?
- It's just over a minute.

525
00:24:02,102 --> 00:24:03,916
We pushed 2 milligram
IV lorazepam.

526
00:24:04,004 --> 00:24:05,183
And the antibiotics
clearly aren't working.

527
00:24:05,267 --> 00:24:06,705
Push another 2 lorazepam.

528
00:24:13,491 --> 00:24:16,408
Why do you look like you just
watched the first two minutes of <i>Up?</i>

529
00:24:19,613 --> 00:24:20,886
I thought Teddy
wasn't gonna get

530
00:24:20,971 --> 00:24:22,767
the help he needed
for his bulimia.

531
00:24:22,852 --> 00:24:26,064
I thought maybe his meddling
brother might make sure he did.

532
00:24:26,517 --> 00:24:28,214
Not a bad plan.

533
00:24:28,299 --> 00:24:31,041
The execution was... flawed.

534
00:24:31,126 --> 00:24:33,324
So congratulations on your
upcoming blowout victory.

535
00:24:33,409 --> 00:24:34,572
[Scoffs]

536
00:24:34,657 --> 00:24:37,112
Help! Someone call the RRT.

537
00:24:37,197 --> 00:24:38,240
I got it.

538
00:24:38,422 --> 00:24:40,502
[Tense music playing]

539
00:24:45,813 --> 00:24:46,813
Teddy.

540
00:24:48,822 --> 00:24:52,767
He's ruptured his esophagus.
Page Dr. Murphy and prep an OR.

541
00:24:56,712 --> 00:24:58,812
[Suspenseful music playing]

542
00:25:04,414 --> 00:25:06,140
[Perez] Chest tube placed.

543
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:08,562
The lung drainage is orange?

544
00:25:09,256 --> 00:25:10,913
What's left of the smoothie.

545
00:25:11,006 --> 00:25:13,007
Advance the endoscope.

546
00:25:13,172 --> 00:25:17,593
He is fortunate that you
responded so quickly, Dr. Perez.

547
00:25:19,554 --> 00:25:22,992
I pushed Teddy to admit
his bulimia to his brother.

548
00:25:23,177 --> 00:25:26,195
They fought,
and then he did this.

549
00:25:27,073 --> 00:25:29,657
Oh. That was...

550
00:25:29,858 --> 00:25:31,199
not helpful.

551
00:25:31,284 --> 00:25:32,618
And there is too much damage

552
00:25:32,703 --> 00:25:34,835
for a primary
esophageal repair.

553
00:25:35,211 --> 00:25:38,494
We can place an endoscopic
stent, wait until edema improves.

554
00:25:38,579 --> 00:25:39,732
It will leak.

555
00:25:39,817 --> 00:25:41,665
What about
using omentum as a patch?

556
00:25:41,750 --> 00:25:43,540
The tissue is too friable.

557
00:25:45,398 --> 00:25:48,524
It's usually for kids, but what
about gastric transposition?

558
00:25:48,960 --> 00:25:50,618
We could resect
the damaged esophagus

559
00:25:50,703 --> 00:25:52,468
and reconstruct it
using stomach tissue.

560
00:25:53,875 --> 00:25:55,687
Good idea, Dr. Perez.

561
00:25:55,885 --> 00:25:57,321
This will improve your score.

562
00:25:57,406 --> 00:25:59,191
We need to open him up.

563
00:26:02,699 --> 00:26:05,285
The abscess is not responding
to the antibiotics.

564
00:26:05,370 --> 00:26:07,360
The sinus infection
is still seeding to the brain.

565
00:26:07,515 --> 00:26:08,980
We could drill
an additional burr hole,

566
00:26:09,064 --> 00:26:10,587
get more aggressive
with the drainage.

567
00:26:10,672 --> 00:26:12,200
The same approach
will get you the same results.

568
00:26:12,284 --> 00:26:13,634
Thanks for
the unhelpful cliche.

569
00:26:13,719 --> 00:26:15,465
[Dr. Reznick] Lily needs
a bifrontal craniotomy

570
00:26:15,549 --> 00:26:17,056
with sinus exenteration.

571
00:26:17,141 --> 00:26:18,322
Remove the skull base
on both sides,

572
00:26:18,406 --> 00:26:19,861
then rebuild it
to stop bacterial entry.

573
00:26:19,945 --> 00:26:22,399
I'm not taking off Lily's
forehead and consigning her

574
00:26:22,499 --> 00:26:23,860
to years
of reconstructive surgeries.

575
00:26:23,944 --> 00:26:25,830
You want to save her life
or protect her pretty face?

576
00:26:25,914 --> 00:26:27,781
Are you seriously accusing me
of acting unethically

577
00:26:27,865 --> 00:26:29,205
because I've been
on two dates with her,

578
00:26:29,289 --> 00:26:30,627
- after your move with the flowers?
- [gasps]

579
00:26:30,711 --> 00:26:32,274
- What move with the flowers?
- Shut up.

580
00:26:32,359 --> 00:26:34,563
I'm accusing you of letting your
medical judgment be clouded

581
00:26:34,647 --> 00:26:35,932
because you don't
want to agree with me.

582
00:26:36,016 --> 00:26:37,946
I'm making the right call
for the patient.

583
00:26:38,031 --> 00:26:39,489
Disagreeing with you
is an unrelated bonus.

584
00:26:39,573 --> 00:26:41,259
Get Lily and the OR prepped.

585
00:26:43,426 --> 00:26:45,211
[Sighs]

586
00:26:45,296 --> 00:26:49,181
[Shaun] Removing the devitalized
segment of the esophagus.

587
00:26:49,669 --> 00:26:51,852
We've got a good plane
of healthy tissue.

588
00:26:53,674 --> 00:26:55,556
Dr. Perez,

589
00:26:55,995 --> 00:26:59,837
you may perform the two-layered,
inverted, hand-sewn anastomosis.

590
00:27:04,032 --> 00:27:05,860
[Tense music playing]

591
00:27:16,740 --> 00:27:18,110
[Sighs]

592
00:27:19,157 --> 00:27:21,467
I had a I-late night
on a research project.

593
00:27:21,815 --> 00:27:23,423
My hands aren't stable enough.

594
00:27:25,823 --> 00:27:27,423
Dr. Powell should take this.

595
00:27:35,677 --> 00:27:37,079
Starting to suture.

596
00:27:47,218 --> 00:27:49,002
I am ready to go home.

597
00:27:49,087 --> 00:27:51,742
I am not,
thanks to Andrews dumping

598
00:27:51,827 --> 00:27:53,994
reconfiguring
the remote interface in my lap.

599
00:27:54,079 --> 00:27:56,274
It's weeks, if not months,
of debugging code.

600
00:27:56,489 --> 00:27:57,931
Well, that was fast.

601
00:27:58,016 --> 00:28:01,453
When I asked Dr. Andrews to assign you
a new project, he could not think of any.

602
00:28:01,538 --> 00:28:03,024
How is your hand?

603
00:28:05,008 --> 00:28:08,610
Annoy... Annoyed, along with the
rest of me. Why would you do that?

604
00:28:08,695 --> 00:28:12,243
Because you have been sad
that we have to wait to have a baby.

605
00:28:12,328 --> 00:28:16,649
Work will be a much better
distraction than restoring an old house.

606
00:28:17,731 --> 00:28:20,763
That's not a judgment
for you to make, Shaun.

607
00:28:20,848 --> 00:28:23,345
I'll pick my own distractions.

608
00:28:23,430 --> 00:28:26,923
[Sighs] And I have been sad.

609
00:28:27,763 --> 00:28:29,896
And that house is just a chance

610
00:28:29,981 --> 00:28:32,852
to make something broken
beautiful again.

611
00:28:33,842 --> 00:28:36,782
So is reconfiguring
the remote interface.

612
00:28:36,907 --> 00:28:39,899
The house feels like
a step forward.

613
00:28:41,971 --> 00:28:44,720
I can really see us being happy
in that home, Shaun.

614
00:28:44,805 --> 00:28:48,134
I just... wish you would
try to see that, too.

615
00:28:51,979 --> 00:28:53,673
Okay.

616
00:28:53,811 --> 00:28:55,811
Okay we can make an offer?

617
00:28:55,896 --> 00:28:59,860
No, I meant, okay, I will try.

618
00:29:01,211 --> 00:29:02,759
Thanks.

619
00:29:03,823 --> 00:29:05,431
I'll see you at home later.

620
00:29:05,912 --> 00:29:08,852
[Gentle music playing]

621
00:29:16,338 --> 00:29:17,339
[Door closes]

622
00:29:19,863 --> 00:29:20,951
Sorry I'm late.

623
00:29:21,126 --> 00:29:22,562
I had an impulse.

624
00:29:22,736 --> 00:29:24,868
<i>NBA 2K.</i>

625
00:29:25,042 --> 00:29:26,415
Prepare to get smoked.

626
00:29:26,500 --> 00:29:29,720
Mm. Tip-off will have to wait.
I'm buried.

627
00:29:29,805 --> 00:29:31,372
Maybe I could help?

628
00:29:31,491 --> 00:29:33,235
Trouble with a case?

629
00:29:33,974 --> 00:29:34,974
Yeah.

630
00:29:36,044 --> 00:29:37,384
My own.

631
00:29:38,012 --> 00:29:39,352
What's happened?

632
00:29:41,211 --> 00:29:44,641
Glassman found movement
in my psoas and glutes.

633
00:29:44,726 --> 00:29:48,120
He and Murphy found
an endoscopic solution.

634
00:29:48,746 --> 00:29:51,290
They'll de-tether your
spinal cord. That's great.

635
00:29:53,021 --> 00:29:55,813
Is there a problem
with the surgical plan?

636
00:29:56,253 --> 00:29:59,438
It's quite elegant. [Sighs]

637
00:29:59,523 --> 00:30:01,376
Then what's holding you back?

638
00:30:04,025 --> 00:30:06,173
I feel like we've been
living in this bubble,

639
00:30:06,258 --> 00:30:09,009
this perfect bubble,

640
00:30:09,960 --> 00:30:12,954
and if I step outside of it,
it will pop.

641
00:30:14,532 --> 00:30:16,056
This surgery...

642
00:30:17,344 --> 00:30:19,110
would change you,

643
00:30:20,584 --> 00:30:22,149
not us.

644
00:30:23,560 --> 00:30:26,584
What we have
isn't going to disappear

645
00:30:26,669 --> 00:30:28,321
if you walk again.

646
00:30:30,572 --> 00:30:32,266
You need to believe that.

647
00:30:33,633 --> 00:30:35,290
I want to.

648
00:30:37,030 --> 00:30:40,220
Please. I can't be the reason
you say no.

649
00:30:40,831 --> 00:30:44,016
[Somber music playing]

650
00:30:48,444 --> 00:30:51,333
We successfully repaired
Teddy's distal esophagus

651
00:30:51,418 --> 00:30:53,904
with reconstructed
stomach tissue.

652
00:30:53,989 --> 00:30:56,034
Teddy will be able to eat
and swallow normally,

653
00:30:56,216 --> 00:30:59,818
but any further purging
will cause irreparable damage.

654
00:31:00,005 --> 00:31:02,536
[Monitor beeping]

655
00:31:04,342 --> 00:31:07,162
I thought we were
finally close again.

656
00:31:08,436 --> 00:31:10,458
He's been hurting, and I...

657
00:31:12,875 --> 00:31:14,411
I had no idea.

658
00:31:18,571 --> 00:31:20,294
[Sniffles]

659
00:31:20,927 --> 00:31:22,880
How do I fix this?

660
00:31:24,774 --> 00:31:29,318
Sometimes... trying to fix
the problem is the problem.

661
00:31:31,033 --> 00:31:33,296
I went through
some tough times, too,

662
00:31:33,381 --> 00:31:38,482
and plenty of people
had ideas about how to fix me.

663
00:31:39,838 --> 00:31:42,333
See, I didn't...
I didn't need that.

664
00:31:43,396 --> 00:31:45,208
I just needed them...

665
00:31:46,559 --> 00:31:52,888
[scoffs] to love me,
broken or not.

666
00:32:02,350 --> 00:32:04,265
Even though
I don't like sanding

667
00:32:04,350 --> 00:32:06,396
and paint is sticky
and smells terrible

668
00:32:06,481 --> 00:32:08,456
and power tools
are loud and dangerous,

669
00:32:08,541 --> 00:32:10,851
I am positive that we,
mostly you,

670
00:32:11,073 --> 00:32:15,406
can make that fixer-upper
into a beautiful home... for us

671
00:32:15,576 --> 00:32:17,335
and the family we will have.

672
00:32:19,086 --> 00:32:22,406
Are you saying
we should buy the house?

673
00:32:23,851 --> 00:32:27,476
If it will make you happy.

674
00:32:28,981 --> 00:32:31,810
I bulldozed you, didn't I?

675
00:32:32,124 --> 00:32:35,719
Yes. But I do not mind.

676
00:32:36,307 --> 00:32:37,594
But I do.

677
00:32:38,418 --> 00:32:40,195
I'm being selfish.

678
00:32:41,612 --> 00:32:43,344
Thank you for letting me.

679
00:32:47,909 --> 00:32:51,280
But the only step forward
I need right now

680
00:32:51,365 --> 00:32:53,437
is one we make together.

681
00:32:54,231 --> 00:32:57,133
Let's find a place
we both love.

682
00:32:58,641 --> 00:33:00,319
That is a good approach.

683
00:33:00,404 --> 00:33:01,450
[Chuckles]

684
00:33:02,386 --> 00:33:05,187
And, also, let's get my hand
checked out. It does really hurt.

685
00:33:08,415 --> 00:33:10,578
[Dr. Park] Advancing
into the abscess.

686
00:33:10,663 --> 00:33:11,867
Couldn't stay away?

687
00:33:11,952 --> 00:33:15,000
[Over intercom] Lily is
my patient. I admitted her.

688
00:33:16,926 --> 00:33:19,833
Resecting last bits of capsule
from the abscess cavity.

689
00:33:22,370 --> 00:33:24,527
Got it. Pulling the scope.

690
00:33:25,853 --> 00:33:26,985
[Monitor alarm]

691
00:33:27,182 --> 00:33:30,055
Heart rate's 32. BP, 210/122.

692
00:33:30,140 --> 00:33:32,278
[Asher] Her brain is starting to
herniate out of the burr holes.

693
00:33:32,362 --> 00:33:34,544
Give 100 grams mannitol,
burst suppress high-dose propofol.

694
00:33:34,628 --> 00:33:36,418
That won't be enough.
Get her CO2 below 30.

695
00:33:36,503 --> 00:33:38,244
[Dr. Park] I'm aware.
Place an EVD.

696
00:33:38,345 --> 00:33:40,629
- Should we pivot to the bifrontal craniotomy?
- No time.

697
00:33:40,714 --> 00:33:43,456
Can you connect the burr holes
and run a small craniotomy flap?

698
00:33:43,822 --> 00:33:46,762
No, but a hemicraniectomy
will reduce the brain pressure.

699
00:33:46,847 --> 00:33:48,649
And then you can debride
the skull-base infection.

700
00:33:48,733 --> 00:33:50,355
- Good.
- Good.

701
00:33:51,736 --> 00:33:53,321
[Asher] Mm, that was hot.

702
00:33:53,578 --> 00:33:55,449
[Quirky music playing]

703
00:34:00,175 --> 00:34:04,721
Doing this surgery
is a good decision.

704
00:34:05,099 --> 00:34:07,603
- I hope so.
- Doubts?

705
00:34:08,218 --> 00:34:12,221
No. I'm a little nervous,
but no doubts.

706
00:34:14,305 --> 00:34:17,479
Thank you both
for not giving up.

707
00:34:19,810 --> 00:34:21,206
You're welcome.

708
00:34:23,603 --> 00:34:25,455
We'll see you in recovery.

709
00:34:33,401 --> 00:34:35,127
Welcome back.

710
00:34:36,300 --> 00:34:38,096
You've got a visitor.

711
00:34:45,173 --> 00:34:46,807
You're okay?

712
00:34:48,881 --> 00:34:50,666
Getting there.

713
00:34:50,833 --> 00:34:54,166
No gym for a while.
You need time to heal.

714
00:34:54,748 --> 00:34:56,424
I'm on it, doc.

715
00:35:01,294 --> 00:35:03,182
Remember when we were kids,

716
00:35:04,142 --> 00:35:06,854
you made me watch
<i>Alien vs. Predator?</i>

717
00:35:08,545 --> 00:35:11,916
I had to let you sleep
in my room for three months.

718
00:35:13,458 --> 00:35:18,573
Turns out, the combined
<i>Alien/Predator</i> canon includes 13 movies.

719
00:35:19,356 --> 00:35:21,385
You and I are gonna
watch them together.

720
00:35:22,949 --> 00:35:25,104
If that's cool with you.

721
00:35:27,313 --> 00:35:29,299
Sounds stupid.

722
00:35:31,349 --> 00:35:32,791
But fun.

723
00:35:33,101 --> 00:35:36,455
[Gentle music playing]

724
00:35:36,697 --> 00:35:38,463
[Chuckles]

725
00:35:52,355 --> 00:35:54,400
Looks like both brothers
are on the mend.

726
00:35:54,784 --> 00:35:57,276
Take video. Maybe Murphy
will give you some points.

727
00:35:57,370 --> 00:35:58,666
[Scoffs]

728
00:35:58,912 --> 00:36:00,213
I'm good.

729
00:36:02,734 --> 00:36:06,627
What happened in the OR when
you handed over the anastomosis?

730
00:36:07,554 --> 00:36:09,635
Just didn't feel like my day.

731
00:36:12,673 --> 00:36:16,706
I devised my
first-year-resident rating system

732
00:36:16,791 --> 00:36:18,073
as a distraction.

733
00:36:18,158 --> 00:36:21,619
It was very complicated and
encouraged too much competition.

734
00:36:21,704 --> 00:36:23,893
So I have decided to retire it.

735
00:36:24,041 --> 00:36:25,839
[Quirky music playing]

736
00:36:49,449 --> 00:36:50,987
You okay?

737
00:36:53,565 --> 00:36:56,089
Easily the worst date
I've ever been on.

738
00:36:56,174 --> 00:36:59,307
Well, the next one, I'll put
the rest of your skull back on.

739
00:37:00,565 --> 00:37:03,635
We have to wait until the swelling
in your brain has gone down.

740
00:37:07,529 --> 00:37:09,307
Am I gonna be okay?

741
00:37:10,469 --> 00:37:13,729
You've got a long road ahead,
but yes.

742
00:37:14,716 --> 00:37:17,924
And you won't be alone.

743
00:37:21,590 --> 00:37:23,596
That's a lot of commitment...

744
00:37:25,237 --> 00:37:29,018
especially when you and
Dr. Reznick don't really seem done.

745
00:37:34,399 --> 00:37:36,140
Thanks for everything...

746
00:37:38,085 --> 00:37:39,799
Dr. Park.

747
00:37:45,048 --> 00:37:46,557
[locker door closes]

748
00:37:48,182 --> 00:37:50,010
I'm glad you didn't move on...

749
00:37:51,315 --> 00:37:53,026
from the case.

750
00:37:54,362 --> 00:37:55,811
Glad you listened.

751
00:37:55,896 --> 00:37:57,323
I'm working on it.

752
00:37:58,911 --> 00:38:01,914
Lily will be lucky to have you
through her recovery,

753
00:38:01,999 --> 00:38:04,666
unless you decided
not to see her anymore.

754
00:38:06,742 --> 00:38:09,455
You were right.
She's a keeper.

755
00:38:11,324 --> 00:38:13,229
Then I'm happy for you two.

756
00:38:13,642 --> 00:38:16,377
[Gentle music playing]

757
00:38:24,457 --> 00:38:26,285
Visiting hours still open?

758
00:38:26,370 --> 00:38:28,721
[Chuckles] They don't usually
let visitors into pre-op.

759
00:38:28,806 --> 00:38:31,385
Well, nobody says no
to a guy in a wheelchair.

760
00:38:31,486 --> 00:38:32,924
I had to see you.

761
00:38:33,366 --> 00:38:39,596
I recognize this is terrible
timing and kind of bonkers,

762
00:38:39,910 --> 00:38:42,487
but I couldn't let you
go in before asking.

763
00:38:45,147 --> 00:38:46,823
Audrey...

764
00:38:48,614 --> 00:38:50,268
[clears throat]

765
00:38:51,240 --> 00:38:52,502
Will you marry me?

766
00:38:52,746 --> 00:38:54,356
[Gentle music playing]

767
00:38:55,796 --> 00:38:57,385
[Exhales sharply]

